-- Vettel Wins Japan Grand Prix as Webber Extends His F-1 Championship Lead
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-10-10T07:40:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/vettel-wins-japanese-grand-prix-as-webber-extends-f-1-championship-lead.html
Sebastian Vettel won the Japanese
Grand Prix ahead of Red Bull teammate Mark Webber, who extended
his lead in the Formula One drivers’ championship.  It was Vettel’s third victory this season and second
straight at the Suzuka circuit. Ferrari’s Fernando Alonso
finished third ahead of McLaren duo Jenson Button and Lewis
Hamilton.  Webber, who had taken an 11-point lead over Fernando Alonso
into today’s race, tops the standings by 14 points over Vettel
and Alonso with three races remaining.  The next event is the Oct. 24 Korean Grand Prix before the
19-race series concludes in Brazil and Abu Dhabi.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  